'''Ebba Lövenskiold''' (born October 7, 1977) is a Swedish journalist and education activist. She has been covering film and entertainment for Swedish newspapers and magazines from [[New York City]] since 2008.
== Together for Better == She is the Founder of the Together for Better Foundation, a charity working for kid´s right to education.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kristianstadsbladet.se/kristianstad/katastrofen-fick-henne-att-agera/|title=Katastrofen fick henne att agera - Kristianstadsbladet|first=Lukas|last=Ernryd|date=10 July 2013|publisher=}}</ref> Through the foundation, Ebba builds and supports schools for underprivileged children in the [[Dominican Republic]]. Ebba started the project after having vacationed on the island when the devastating earthquake hit [[Haiti]] in 2010. The charity funded construction of three schools.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plazakvinna.com/noje_kultur/portratt/langlasning-ebba-bytte-vardag-fran-nyc-till-dominikanska-republiken/|title=Långläsning: Ebba bytte vardag – från NYC till Dominikanska Republiken|publisher=}}</ref>
