{{no footnotes|date=May 2017}} '''Marc Coppey''' (born 1969 in Strasbourg) is a French contemporary classical [[cellist]].
== Biography == In 1988, Marc Coppey attracted the attention of the world of music by winning the two highest prizes of the [[International Johann Sebastian Bach Competition]] - the first prize and the special prize for Bach's best performance - at 18. He was then noticed by [[Yehudi Menuhin]].
He made his debut in Moscow then in Paris in the Tchaikovsky trio with Menuhin and [[Viktoria Postnikova]], on the occasion of a concert filmed by [[Bruno Monsaingeon]]. [[Rostropovitch]] invited him to the Evian Festival and, from then on, his soloist career unfolded under the direction of [[Emmanuel Krivine]], [[Rafael Frühbeck de Burgos]], [[Michel Plasson]], [[Jean-Claude Casadesus]], [[Theodor Guschlbauer]], [[John Nelson (conductor)|John Nelson]], [[Raymond Leppard]], [[Erich Bergel]], [[Philippe Bender]], [[Alan Gilbert (conductor)|Alan Gilbert]], [[Lionel Bringuier]], [[Paul McCreesh]], [[Yutaka Sado]], [[Kirill Karabits]] and [[Asher Fisch]].
== External links == * [http://www.marccoppey.com Official website] * {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=q18727}} (discography) * [http://www.satirino.fr/fr/artists/marc-coppey Artistes · Solistes · Marc Coppey · violoncelle] on Satirino * [http://www.telerama.fr/musique/archet-complet-le-violoncelliste-marc-coppey,28641.php Archet complet, le violoncelliste Marc Coppey] on ''[[Télérama]]'' (10 May 2008) * [https://www.narbonne-classic-festival.fr/artistes-musiciens/marc-coppey/ Marc Coppey] on Narbonne-classic-festival.fr * [http://www.les-musicales.com/fr/le-festival/marc-coppey Marc Coppey] on Les Musicales * [https://www.francemusique.fr/personne/marc-coppey-0 Marc Coppey] on [[France Musique]] * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P9Rv7V413I4 Marc Coppey - "Suites pour violoncelle" de/von Bach – ARTE Concert] on YouTube {{Authority control}}
