{{ Infobox University |name =Oguz Han Engineering and Technology University of Turkmenistan |image = |established = 2016 |type = University | |district = |city = [[Ashgabat]] | |country = [[Turkmenistan]] | |Website = }} '''Oguz Han Engineering and Technology University of Turkmenistan''' ({{lang-tk|'''Türkmenistanyň Oguz han adyndaky Inžener-tehnologiýalar uniwersiteti'''}}) is a university located in [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]]. The University was established in 2016.
== History == Oguz Han Engineering and Technology University of Turkmenistan was established as an important step towards deepening the Turkmen–Japan partnership in science and education.<ref name="tdh">{{cite web|url=http://tdh.gov.tm/news/en/articles.aspx&article7006&cat26|title=Head of Turkmenistan and President of Japan’s University of Tsukuba Discuss Aspects of Cooperation in Science and Education|website=TDH|accessdate=2017-08-18}}</ref> It is the 19th of civil higher education institutions of Turkmenistan.<ref name="erasmusplus">{{cite web|url=http://www.erasmusplus.org.tm/en/higher-education-in-turkmenistan/turkmen-universities/|title=Turkmen Universities &#124; National Erasmus+ Office in Turkmenistan|website=erasmusplus.org.tm|accessdate=2017-08-18}}</ref> It partially uses premises of [[International Turkmen-Turkish University]] in Koshi area Project street of Ashgabat.
